                            <comment id="13589972" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 22:01:22 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Being able to have multiple tables as your input path&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Being able to filter on specific columns/column families&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;MultiTableInputFormat&lt;/tt&gt; provides both of these requests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Providing the source location (table/row/column) to the results&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;Result&lt;/tt&gt; instances provided to the mapper satisfy row and column. Table would be an addition. Perhaps &lt;tt&gt;map.input.file&lt;/tt&gt; can be used to deliver the table name?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multiple clusters&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is tricky as it amounts to setting multiple conf objects for the job. From the client perspective, it could be passed in as a &lt;tt&gt;List&amp;lt;Configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; in the same way &lt;tt&gt;initTableMapper&lt;/tt&gt; already accepts a &lt;tt&gt;List&amp;lt;Scan&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;. Do you have any ideas on implementation?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Different schemas&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This request doesn&apos;t make sense to me. How do you mean?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15671611" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2016 20:59:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented elsewhere. See MultiTableInputFormat and MultiTableOutputFormat.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
